data.description: Lets take a walk along the lush brome field and crest the hill of this lovely 30acres to get a truly amazing view of what this property has to offer. This property has bluestem prairie grass and a few buffalo wallows dot the hillside, taking you back in time to when the buffalo grazed this area. Electric, Rural Water, and Fiberoptic at the road. Build a home on the ridge and have views for days or consider the lower brome field that runs along Hopkins Switch! The 2023 brome hay production remains with the Seller and will be harvested between late June and early August. Don't miss this opportunity to have paved road frontage just minutes from Douglass and easy access on 77 Hwy to 400 Hwy, Rose Hill, or even Winfield.
